subtitle: in the shallow Waters off its eastern
shore stands an unfathomable Stone
complex 92 artificial eyelets built on
top of a coral reef over an area a mile
long all linked by an elaborate network
of stone lined
canals these Stone canals give the place
its name nonmodal which translates to
within the
intervals in more modern times nonmodal
has been given another name the Venice
of the Pacific
it is not hard to see why throughout the
complex are a series of unbelievable
structures made from enormous balt
Stones walls standing as high as 58 ft
tall and measuring as much as 17 ft
thick columns and buildings all made
from Stones which weigh anywhere from 5
to 50 tons stacked in the manner which
one might construct a log cabin
